[wiki]NewD3[/wiki] (as designed by [user]RadiantCowbells[/user]):

[table][row][cell][/cell][cell]A[/cell][cell]B[/cell][cell]C[/cell][/row]
[row][cell]Mafia[/cell][cell][color=red]Mafia Roleblocker[/color][/cell][cell][color=red]Mafia Rolecop[/color][/cell][cell][color=red]Mafia Goon[/color][/cell][/row]
[row][cell]Row 1[/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Cop and Town Doctor[/color][/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Tracker and Town Friendly Neighbor[/color][/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Cop and Vanilla Townie[/color][/cell][/row]
[row][cell]Row 2[/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Jailkeeper and Town Tracker[/color][/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Jailkeeper and Town Friendly Neighbor[/color][/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Jailkeeper and Vanilla Townie[/color][/cell][/row]
[row][cell]Row 3[/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Mason and Town Mason[/color][/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Tracker and Town Doctor[/color][/cell][cell][color=forestgreen]Town Mason and Town Mason[/color][/cell][/row][/table]
Each Newbie Game will be given a setup that incorporates one mafia role from the top of a column, and then two town roles from a row below the selected mafia role.  The remaining six roles will be filled in by [color=red]one mafia goon[/color] and [color=forestgreen]five vanilla townies[/color] appropriately, to create a [color=red]2-mafia[/color] and [color=forestgreen]7-town[/color] setup.

All Newbie games use the [wiki]Natural Action Resolution[/wiki] system for determining Night action effects.  [color=red]Mafia Roleblocker [/color] action takes precedence over a [color=forestgreen]Town Jailkeeper[/color] action should that apply.

Mafia are able to communicate in their Private Topic at all times.[/area]

